26/02/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU Economic and Monetary Affairs Commissioner Olli Rehn announced on Thursday (February 25th) that he plans to visit Greece on Monday, to discuss efforts to reduce the country's huge budget deficit and bring its soaring debts under control. Before heading to Athens, Rehn will be briefed by EU financial experts who wrapped up a visit of their own Thursday, aimed at analysing reforms proposed by the government. (AP, AFP, ANA-MPA - 25/02/10)
